 Edo governor, Godwin Obaseki<br />Photo: Twitter/GovernorObaseki  Addressing reporters at Benin airport, he described the reports as “fake news.” The governor, who has been on vacation, resumed work after his one-month yearly leave during which his deputy, Philip Shaibu, acted. “I feel very good, refreshed and ready to resume work,” he said. On hand to receive the governor were members and leaders of the APC, State Executive Council, socio-cultural groups as well as youths under the Coalition of Edo Returnees. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .